    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-03-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="4"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d4">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Roosevelt Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">President <persName type="from">Roosevelt</persName> to Prime
                        Minister <persName type="to">Churchill</persName>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d4fn1">Sent to the United States Naval Attaché, London, via
                        Navy channels.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-03-22">22 March
                            1944</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Number 507. Personal and secret. From the President for the <gloss
                        target="#t_FormerNavalPerson1">Former Naval Person</gloss>.</p>
                <p>Your 629<note n="2" xml:id="d4fn2">
                        <hi rend="italic">Supra</hi>.</note> received and my Chiefs of Staff have
                    been told.</p>
                <p>I join you in hoping that we may arrange to have a meeting before the great event
                    is launched.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Roosevelt</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
